Reasoning: The paper deals with developing a method to discover common motifs in noisy time series data and leverage those motifs to more robustly assign states to measurements. This involves formulating the problem of motif discovery as a large optimization problem, which is solved using an expectation-maximization type approach. The paper also discusses experiments on synthetic data and two case studies on real-world time series data. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper deals with systems and control (cs.SY) and social and information networks (cs.SI) as it discusses the application of the method to financial markets.
